div.p:
As for political settlement, my Government has been doing its part for peace in
                    every forum, at every level and at every hour, both before and since the
                    outbreak of hostilities. We have consistently upheld the principles which I
                    stated publicly and repeated to you at Glassboro: 

First, the recognized right of national life;

Second, justice for the refugees;

Third, innocent maritime passage;

Fourth, limits on the wasteful and destructive arms race; and

Fifth, political independence and territorial integrity for
                            all.
